manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Small White Side End Tables - Intriguing Design & Exact Engineering This pretty cute and simple white side table is made of PVC, very smooth to the touch and surely easy to clean. With intriguing design, all the pieces snap together, no trouble snapping as instructed. It can be used to store small books, magazine, toys or knickknacks or other small stuffs. Suitable for any places, such as living room, bedroom, bathroom, toddlers room, dorm or office etc.

A Nice Looking Small End Side Table in Your House - Functional & Attractive As a side table or nightstand to put your lamp, humidifier or photos; As a small bathroom table to store your makeup, bath towels, As a display shelf for small plants, toys or knickknacks; As a kitchen storage organizer for storing some snacks and foods; As a bookcase or bookshelf to store small size books Such a small side table is great for someone who has no tools or not great at building things, shelf snaps together easily. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Purchased to use as a side table during the holidays when everything was out of place. It is lightweight. It snaps together and is secured with a couple of screws after the holidays. I ended up using it in my laundry room. This is not a really sturdy table. It is for lightweight storage or decoration.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: You can assemble it with your eyes closed, very easy. It’s small and cute and hold everything.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works for what I wanted
reviews.reviewText: Definitely cheap and not what I was expecting. Most of the connections are cut grooves and are much more visible in person then the pictures. Everything did go together easily by hand and seemed sturdy enough but I would not trust anything heavy on it. It’s a very light composite type plastic, almost foam like inside.I bought 2, stained and sealed a 12” wide board and screwed it to the tops to make a nice fireplace mantle/table to replace an old dark faux mantle that blocked windows and made the room too dark. It worked great for my project but honestly if they were going to be out in the open and used as end tables I would have probably returned them. They just look a little to cheesy for that to me with the jigsaw puzzle construction and very visible screws. They are cheap and an easy storage fix for a small space if you don’t mind the look or it’s tucked away mostly out of view.Packaged wellFast shippingEasy assemblyRelatively sturdyLight weightSmall sizeSlightly lacking appearance with so many visible joints and hardware

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quick to put together!
reviews.reviewText: From unboxing to placing my items on/in the shelf, it took approximately 12min total!The instructions were extremely simple to follow, all necessary tools & screws were included and gloves were added in for those that may need/want them while building.The material feels like foam? Not exactly particle board but a blend of wood & foam? Either way - it’s very light weight, easy on the eyes & fairly easy to build.You’ll need to apply some weight on the product when shoving in the “puzzle pieces” so a rubber mallet *may* be required for some people, but a firm palm slap will also do the trick. Just remember the material that you’re working with as to not apply so much force that you end up snapping a piece or breaking an entry point.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Would give this negative zero Stars if that was an option, The term you get what you pay for is too nice for this! Made of cheap flimsy cardboard type material when you assemble it the pieces don't fit and if you bang them in lightly they completely crack. 100% junk do not waste your money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble? What?
reviews.reviewText: First of all, this was incredibly difficult to put together. It wasn’t confusing, just physically a challenge to make the pieces fit together.Not sure if the pieces I got were cut wrong, but the info says you MIGHT need a small hammer to assemble. No, you WILL need that hammer. Even with it, you risk breaking the flimsy wood (I did end up breaking a small piece off because you basically have to force the pieces together). Also, use the screws provided to give it a little more stability.Looks nice, will serve the purpose I need it for (coffee stand for home office), but it’s not worth the $30 price. Good luck finding something cheaper that looks half this nice, though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I was looking for!
reviews.reviewText: I have a disability so my son assembled this for me in less than 10 minutes. Its sturdy and is the right size for the space I wanted to put it. It holds standard height ring binders (or smaller) and doesn't wobble. Its a handy little product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Little Table/Book shelf
reviews.reviewText: This is the best little table! I have two of them now. One we have by the bed for my husband to put his CPAP machine on. The other we have on our porch between our rocking chairs. Made out of PVC, it should last forever! It is a great product. The pieces fit together very well. It even came with gloves to wear while putting the pieces together so you don't hurt your hands. There are no rough edges. The instructions are excellent with pictures to explain how to do it. It took me about 10 minutes to assemble. It even came with the right size screwdriver. What company ever sends the equipment to assemble like that! I am very, very pleased with this inexpensive but durable table. Excellent product!!!!

I love this little shelf! I actually purchased two and stuck them together to create a custom square end table to fit in the space beside my couch and to match the rest of my farmhouse style furniture/decor. The material of this shelf kind of surprised me as it’s not wood, it’s kind of like a thick and dense foam board. But you can’t tell unless you touch it, and it seems strong enough! They’re also extremely easy to assemble, it took me about 10 minutes each.
Just the right size for our bedroom.
The size is small and light weight, over all product is really good.
All the joins look like this, terrible material like putting a 3d puzzle together.. I would give 0 stars if I could

I understand the jigsaw puzzle concept of building this item but it’s very hard to fit the pieces together especially the final piece. Fitting it in cracked a piece. Luckily I managed to fit it in and it’s hard to notice. For this reason I would not recommend this item. Not worth the price point. It’s not a very good “put together item” This should sell for 15.00 to 20.00 less. Once together pieces are not tight and neat.
